 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukelvyntelarian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelvyn Telarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 1:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Half -Full</span><hr size=1> As far as these threads of late, I am solidly in the glass-half-full camp, and applaud folks like Beryl and Sam.  One thing that is a source of irritation is when folks keep posting that bla,bla...is how such-and-such was originally intended.  <br>
<br>
Well, how would anyone know?  Do they work for VI?  Please don't drag out the original Wizard description or any hack-garbage from Beta. The class is intended as the designers make it, and evolves in the manner they hope for it to change, even if their intentions are stupid. In other words, it does not mean that their ideas don't suck, because many of them certainly do.  It just means that saying something is not how the makers intended, when the complainant is not the maker, is ludicrous. <br>
<br>
It's not that constructive criticism of VI's changes and designs cannot be helpful, but the constant negativity associated with a lot of these posts does more to hurt the Wizard class than help--talk about damage over time.  <br>
<br>
Many people accuse the more optimistic Wizards of having their heads in the sand, but I would assert clinging to some old moldy fantasy that some of these things are gonna be changed is the worst kind of denial. However, it definately does an effective job disuading people from wanting to make or group with a Wizard. I am not saying that other things might not be changed, but some of them are clearly closed cases--accept it.<br>
<br>
Some would argue that if it weren't for some of the massive flames and protests in the past directed at VI, that many of the good changes we have gotten would never have happened.  All I can say to that is, whatever in the world would give such people the idea that VI changed the things as the result of them? Rather narcisistic and egocentric, I would think.<br>
<br>
Futhermore, seeing the glass-half-full does not mean there aren't problems.  It just means that focusing on the useful aspects that are present and maximizing them can be a more effective means of change than the opposite. Quite frankly, human nature, and Nature itself,  tends to prefer to invest in the more successful concerns in life than in the lesser ones. Constantly presenting yourselves as failures and useless certainly is effective at fulfilling that. And just dropping in the qualifyer &quot;I'm not saying we are useless...BUT....&quot;  does not eliminate the erosion that overall negativity can have.<br>
<br>
I am very pleased to see several people stepping up and taking a more optimistic position, and am glad to hear stories of Wizard success, effectiveness, and new applications.  I am also glad to see many of the more depricating posts being moved to the Rants Forum (though some really positive and useful posts, particularly one about AoE that Beryl posted, got moved to Rants, wrongly I would suggest--that one really had to power to help some new Wizzys and inspire them, but perhaps that is being suppressed here?).<br>
<br>
At any rate, I will go back to happily and successfully playing my Wizard.  Yes, I will chime in with everyone of issues that seem reasonable to me and that should strongly be brought to VI's attention. But, if some of you insist on continuing to play by the Melee classes rules, then enjoy.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kel,55,Ixtlan<br>
Veeshan<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
P.S. Yes, I already thought of the joke--&quot;Half-full of what?&quot;  There, that should prime you for your witty reparte. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uberylshadowhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beryl Shadowhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 1:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues, Wizards, and Damage</span><hr size=1> Heh, just whacked Velk, he's such a wuss.<br>
